  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Benue Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">200 households each receive 3 blankets, 3 sleeping mats, 500 grams of bathing soap, 2 kg for laundry, rechargeable solar lantern for lighting and a small kerosene stove for cooking and heating</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; An estimated 110,000 people were reportedly displaced (SEMA) 

 &#x2022; 21 Local Government Areas affected including Makurdi, Apa, Agatu, Otukpo, Guma, Buruku, Tarka, and Kasina-Ala Local Government Areas of Benue State. 

&#x2022; There were confirmed cases of deaths as a result of the flood.   

&#x2022;.1,503 houses were affected in Benue communities. UNHCR reached 500 households with non-food items 

&#x2022; 2 camps have been set up in Makurdi to accommodate those rendered homeless. At Makurdi International Market and Padopads Secondary School a total of 4,775 people have been registered from 546 households.</narrative>
  </description>
